# Linear Integration Rules

## Automatic Issue Creation

When the user discusses:
- A new feature idea → Create Linear issue with "Feature" label
- A bug or problem → Create Linear issue with "Bug" label
- An improvement → Create Linear issue with "Improvement" label
- A task to do → Create Linear issue with "Task" label

## Issue Creation Parameters

Always use these settings:
```json
{
  "team": "WeTest",
  "project": "WeApply - AI Refinement",
  "assignee": "pelle@weapply.se",
  "labels": ["Development", "<type_label>", "<tech_label>"]
}
```

## Label Selection Guide

### Type Labels (pick ONE)
- `Bug` - Something broken
- `Feature` - New functionality
- `Improvement` - Enhancement
- `Task` - General work

### Tech Labels (pick if relevant)
- `Backend` - Server/API work
- `Frontend` - UI work
- `AI/ML` - AI-related
- `Integration` - Third-party

## Status Updates

When work is completed on an issue:
1. Update issue status to "Done" or appropriate state
2. Add comment with implementation summary
3. Reference commit/PR if applicable
4. **Update project documentation** (see Documentation section)

## Documentation Maintenance

### ALWAYS Update After Changes

**Linear Project Document** (System Overview):
- Document ID: `87ad9c07-f9fe-42fe-8ea6-60c1687548fa`
- URL: https://linear.app/weapply/document/system-overview-3181a0fdda51
- Contains: System flow, features, labels, configuration
- **Must be kept current with implemented features**

Use `mcp_linear_update_document` to update when:
- New features are implemented
- Configuration changes
- Labels or priority rules change
- System flow is modified

**Local Documentation**:
- Update `REFINEMENT_PLAN.md` with feature status
- Update README.md if setup changes

## Conversation Tracking

If a conversation leads to actionable items:
1. Summarize into discrete issues
2. Create each as separate Linear issue
3. Link related issues using `relatedTo` parameter

## Example Usage

```typescript
// When user says "Let's add dark mode support"
mcp_linear_create_issue({
  title: "Add dark mode support to admin panel",
  team: "WeTest",
  project: "WeApply - AI Refinement",
  assignee: "pelle@weapply.se",
  labels: ["Feature", "Development", "Frontend"],
  description: "## Overview\nAdd dark mode toggle...\n\n## Requirements\n- ..."
})
```
